CARDIO GOOD FITNESS

Data Description¶

The data is about customers of the treadmill product(s) of a retail store called Cardio Good Fitness. It contains the following variables-

  • 1.Product - The model no. of the treadmill
  • 2.Age - Age of the customer in no of years
  • 3.Gender - Gender of the customer
  • 4.Education - Education of the customer in no. of years
  • 5.Marital Status - Marital status of the customer
  • 6.Usage - Avg. # times the customer wants to use the treadmill every week
  • 7.Fitness - Self rated fitness score of the customer (5 - very fit, 1 - very unfit)
  • 8.Income - Income of the customer
  • 9.Miles- Miles that a customer expects to run

<Figure size 648x432 with 0 Axes>

  • From our Univariative Analysis, we deduced that TM195 was the most sold product model with TM498 behind and TM798 taking the last place.
  • But from our Multivariative Analysis, We can notice that when we compare the income level to the various product, we can see that customers who tend to buy the product model TM798 have high a Income as compared to the other products.
  • From this we can deduce that TM798 is more expensive as compared to TM195 and TM498 hence customers with high income go for this option.
  • We can also determine that higher number of education years means a higher income range.

<Figure size 648x432 with 0 Axes>
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  • Now from the plot above, we can clearly see that yes indeed the most bought Product is TM195 but there is something else.
  • We see that for Males, the second most bought Product is the TM798 and for females is the least bought and the margin between TM498 AND TM798 is huge.
  • Since we realised previously that customers with a high income tend to go for TM798 we need to verify if yes indeed the male category have a higher salary Range as compared to females.
  • From the first plot we can see that Males tend to have a higher salary range than females which is why TM798 which is the most expensive Product is bought more by males and less by females.
  • Also, a high number of education years means a high range of income

Customer Characteristics¶

  • Majority of Customers are Partnered up and with more of them being males. A customer with a a lot of years in education has a higher probability of having a higher range of income as compared to a customer who does not. Majority of these customers with high income range tend to Purchase The TM798 model which was analysed that might be the most expensive model.High income customers who purchase the TM798 Model also have a high fitness level.

Conclusion¶

  • The Dataset for Cardio Good Fitness has been analysed to get insights on customer/consumer characteristics which will be beneficial to stakeholders. The various analysis and visualisations have given some insights which cane be summarised below:
    1. There are 9 categories in this data among which we have the various types of Product Model and the customer segments.We also have a breakdown of the Income level,fitness,age,number of years in education and the Miles a customer Run.
    1. The data is small but a few insights were made and these insights may change as we get more observations on the data.
    1. We saw that the most Purchased Product Model from the retail store is the TM195 with TM498 in second place and then TM798 is the least bought out of the three.But upon further analysis, it was noticed that when we take the various customer segments based on their income, we notice that individuals with higher income tend to purchase the TM798 Model and also among the Male customer, TM798 is the second Model with the highest number of purchases and the least purchased among females.
    1. Higher number of years in Education gives a higher range of income. i.e customers with a lot of years in education tend to have higher income Range.
    1. A customer with a partnered Marital status has a higher probability of purchasing a Product as compared to the singles.
    1. Lastly customers with high fitness ratings tend to be customers who have the TM798 model.Same as those with higher miles run.

Recommendations¶

    1. Cardio Good Fitness should focus their sales more on potential customers who are Partnered since those individuals have a higher probability to buy from them and it will help in targeted marketing which makes sales faster and convenient
    1. Cardio Good Fitness should engage in advertisements that attract middle aged adults preferable between the ages of 25-40.This includes the use of billboards since majority of these age segment are working class people and will probably pass by multiple billboards on their way to work and also on their way home from work. Also they can utilise advertising channels like Radio and news platforms since these customer segments are more likely to engage with these channels.
  • 3.Cardio Good Fitness should develop a strategy that focuses sales more on Families and couples since majority of customers from this data are partnered. A single customer is likely to purchase one but a partnered up customer is likely to buy 2 or more for the family.
    1. Lastly, Cardio Good Fitness should develop a score metric like an RFM(Recency frequency and Monetary) that can give you more insights on your most valuable customers and others to be able to keep and know and understand their customers better.
